Re: Setting up multiple bitcoin machines behind NAT

Bitcointalk

2010-05-16 23:56:03 UTC - [11]Original Post

   At the moment, it always assumes the incoming port is 8333, so it would
   tell other bitcoin nodes to connect to router:8333 even if youʼre
   redirecting from another port number.
   Iʼm not in a big hurry to fix this because I canʼt think of any benefit
   to having more than one incoming connection port.  If youʼre providing
   one incoming port, then youʼve done your bit to help the network.
   Having two incoming ports to the same person doesnʼt help redundancy.
   If you have many computers, then using the -connect switch on most of
   them to connect locally makes more sense.
